Please make sure you have not installed Chrome by other means in
you Slackware box. This package can install it for you and maintain
it updated afterwards.

To install this program you need to be root and issue the following:

mkdir /opt/google-chrome-the-latest
cp google-chrome-the-latest.py /opt/google-chrome-the-latest
chmod +x /opt/google-chrome-the-latest/google-chrome-the-latest.py
cp google-chrome-the-latest-cron.sh /etc/cron.hourly
chmod +x /etc/cron.hourly/google-chrome-the-latest-cron.sh

Thats it!

Now you can start the chrome install simply by running:
/opt/google-chrome-the-latest/google-chrome-the-latest.py install

In any event this program will notify you within on hour
that a new Chrome is available for you to install.

Optionally you may want force the USERNAME variable at the
google-chrome-the-latest-cron.sh file to your username.
